# Running stylua

`stylua.toml` lives at the **repo root**, and stylua does **not** search parent
directories by default. Running it from a subdirectory (e.g.
`nvim/.config/nvim`) silently falls back to stylua defaults and reports bogus
diffs (double quotes, call parens) that contradict this repo's style.

Always run stylua from the repo root, or point it at the root config. Do not
"run, fail, hunt for the config, rerun" — use one of these the first time:

```bash
# From the repo root (preferred — config is auto-discovered):
stylua --check path/to/file.lua

# From anywhere:
stylua --check --search-parent-directories path/to/file.lua
```

The same applies to formatting (drop `--check`). luacheck/selene are unaffected.
